speech.p:
asked the Minister of Agriculture (1) whether he will give an assurance that he will not allow further labour and materials to be used in metalling spur or lateral roads up the fell sides in the vicinity of the Ennerdale Forest Road;


(2) whether, in vie of the greater urgency of other road building projects and the need for employing all available manpower on work of vital importance, he will suspend work on the Ennerdale Forest Road in the Lake District;

(3) what are the reasons which make the existing Ennerdale Forest Road unsuitable for moving the short and light trimmings which will alone be ready for transportation in the next few years from the plantings up this valley.

Notes:—


1. The above figures cover:


(a) Land held under requisition by committees (including land on which the requisition has been transferred from a Service Department): 357,197 acres;

(b) Land requisitioned or owned by Service Departments, but being cultivated under arrangements made with Committees: 114,966 acres;

(c) Former grassland improvement stations under lease to the Minister: 2,180 acres.


2. Of the total of 474,343 acres, some 257,040 acres are being farmed direct by committees and the remainder has been let.
